entries.entry: I tried to be happy that I was at work. But I forgot my lunch. I hate it.
I woke up this morning ready to take on the day. I went to the bathroom and saw that my cat has started messing with the toilet paper again.
Work was great! My boss bought us lunch and everybody was excited. I got all of my work done and was able to leave work on time
I was able to make time for yoga and meditation, which I was very proud of.
I spoke to an old friend from high school who just had a baby that look like Eddie Murphy.
My co-worker and I presented our projects to the Director of the company on ways to improve the company. He was very proud.
I spoke to my parents for 3 1/2 hours today. It was a very pleasant conversation.
I woke up this morning, feeling great. It's Friday, less work, more fun.
I met my friends downtown to have fun in the city. It was needed and we danced the night away.
I woke up with the worst hangover in the morning. I am out of cofee. Rent is due. I have to go the grocery store.
I went to the grocery store, played with my cat, wrote a lot in my journal, and caught up on my TV shows.
I was able to do yoga and meditate this morning. I met my parents for brunch today. We laughed and hugged very much.
My friend came over for a playdate with her dog. We binged watch movies, drank wine, and talked about what was happening in our lives.
